title: For Sale:  Ruger Mk IV .22lr
postcontent: The Ruger .22 pistols have ben highly regarded for decades for their accuracy and reliability, but if you've ever owned one before you'll know that those benefits come at a price: Depending on your level of mechanical inclination, they can be a real pain in the neck to put back together after field stripping. No doubt many a local gunsmith has made a decent amount of money off of folks who show up at their doors with a bunch of Ruger .22 bits in a bag and a defeated look on their faces.Well, it only took Ruger a few decades but with the new Mark IV series of pistols, they've directly addressed those complaints. What used to take a thorough reading of the manual, followed by cursing, followed by YouTube videos, followed by more cursing, now takes about ten seconds and can be done blindfolded. The Mark IV also features a CNC machined frame and ambidextrous safety. Comes with two magazines.
